DOCUMENT();
############################################################ # Load Macros ############################################################ loadMacros( "PGstandard.pl", "PGML.pl", "AnswerFormatHelp.pl", "PCCmacros.pl", "parserFormulaWithUnits.pl", "contextForm.pl", "contextFraction.pl", "parserLinearRelation.pl", "PGcourse.pl", ); COMMENT('Authored in PreTeXt');
############################################################ # Header ############################################################ TEXT(beginproblem());
############################################################ # PG Setup Code ############################################################ Context("Fraction"); $rate = Fraction(random(1,11),12); $speed = FormulaWithUnits("$rate ft"); $initial = random(4,6); $final = random(10,12); Context("LinearRelation")->variables->are(t => 'Real'); $equation = LinearRelation("$initial + $rate t = $final");
############################################################ # Body ############################################################
BEGIN_PGML Read the scenario. Then write a complete sentence that defines a variable to use. Lastly, write an equation to model the scenario. There is no need to solve the equation.
You planted a young tree in front of your house, and it was [`[$initial]`] feet tall. Ever since, it has been growing by [`[$speed]`] each year. How many years will it take for the tree to grow to be [`[$final]`] feet tall? Write an equation to model this scenario. There is no need to solve it.
[@KeyboardInstructions('Use [|t|]* as the variable.')@]**
[_]{$equation}{20}
END_PGML
